Sam has been president since 2008, and will take charge of his final term lasting another four years. JOHANNESBURG Gideon Sam was re-elected as the president of South African Sports Confederation and Olympic Committee at their elections on Saturday afternoon.Sam has been president since 2008, and will take charge of his final term lasting another four years.Hajera Kajee was elected as the deputy-president, while Barry Hendricks will take over as the vice-president and replaces Jace Naidoo.The rest of the board will comprise of Kobus Marais, Merryl King, Les Williams, and Debbie Alexander.South African Rugby Union s Mark Williams was also elected into a spot on the board.